migalife 1.09
Copyright 2007-2019 miga Software

This program implements the famous hashlife algorithm invented by Bill Gosper in the early 1980s. Many thanks to Tomas Rokicki whose article "An algorithm for compressing space and time" - http://www.ddj.com/hpc-high-performance-computing/184406478 - gave me all the useful information to write migalife.

Compilation
-----------

Unix 32 bits     cd unix
                 ./make32.sh
Unix 64 bits     cd unix
                 ./make64.sh
Windows 32 bits  use Visual C++ solution windows/migalife32.sln
Windows 64 bits  use Visual C++ solution windows/migalife64.sln

Binaries
--------

Unix 32 bits Release     unix/migalife32.exe
Unix 32 bits Debug       unix/migalife32_debug.exe
Unix 64 bits Release     unix/migalife64.exe
Unix 64 bits Debug       unix/migalife64_debug.exe
Windows 32 bits Release  windows/migalife32/Release/migalife32.exe
Windows 32 bits Debug    windows/migalife32/Debug/migalife32.exe
Windows 64 bits Release  windows/migalife64/Release/migalife64.exe
Windows 64 bits Debug    windows/migalife64/Debug/migalife64.exe

Usage
-----

[binary] [-h] [-l level | -g generation] [-n nodes] [-c] [-p] [-r rules] [-i input] [-f file] [-o output] [-v]

-h  hashlife mode, default conventional mode.
-l  run generation 2**level, default run forever.
-g  run given generation, default run forever.
-n  static allocation for nodes, default dynamic.
-c  collect free nodes.
-p  compute population.
-r  life rules in format survival/birth, default 23/3 or rules given in input.
-i  input format 1 rle/2 lif/3 hlf, default 1.
-f  name of input file, default standard input.
-o  output format 1 none/2 view/3 file, default 1.
-v  verbose mode.

Patterns
--------

I have gathered some patterns from Golly - http://golly.sourceforge.net - in the rle folder and from Alan Hensel's collection - http://www.ibiblio.org/lifepatterns - in the lif folder.

Viewer commands
---------------

[n]nw  northwest n levels down
[n]ne  northeast n levels down
[n]sw  southwest n levels down
[n]se  southeast n levels down
[n]u   n levels up
q      quit

hlf format
----------

This file format can be used as both input and output. It contains the canonilized quadtree data generated by migalife from a lif or rle pattern or from another hlf file. A sample file is available in the hlf folder.
